'''[[active]] [[front]]'''
#{{Physics}}[[Meteorology]]. The [[boundary]] between two different air masses, or a portion thereof, which produces [[appreciable]] [[cloud]]iness and [[precipitation]] and is usually accompanied by significant shifts in [[wind]] direction. [[adiabatic]] [[lapse]] rate-the rate of decrease of temperature with height of a parcel of dry air lifted upward through the atmosphere with no addition or deletion of heat. 

